            {
              "id": 847881,
              "key": "8929d89a-327d-4ace-aa91-4a2e39c6e226",
              "title": null,
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "## Data storytelling is critical for anyone working with data\n\nData storytelling is an important skill that any data analyst or data engineer should aim to include in their skill set. \n\n* Here is a [Forbes article](https://www.forbes.com/sites/brentdykes/2016/03/31/data-storytelling-the-essential-data-science-skill-everyone-needs/#2fceeb5e52ad) that highlights this need.\n* Another Forbes article that emphasizes the need to [telling stories from data](https://www.forbes.com/sites/nicolemartin1/2018/11/01/data-visualization-how-to-tell-a-story-with-data/#49d20b624368)\n* Here is another link that talks about [how choosing visualization is important](https://www.columnfivemedia.com/data-storytelling-brands-data-visualization).\n* [Harvard Business Review](https://hbr.org/2013/04/how-to-tell-a-story-with-data) also talked about this in their 2013 article. \n\nSo as you can see, knowing how to tell stories from your data is a key skill you want to focus on mastering in addition to your data science tool kit.",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            }
          ]
        },
